<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 11:49PM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN ELKHART...
NORTHWESTERN KOSCIUSKO AND NORTHEASTERN MARSHALL COUNTIES THROUGH
1230 AM EDT...
At 1149 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bourbon, or near Bremen, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
